China: The Eastern Wei general Emperor Wenxuan of Northern Qi deposed Xiaojing and established the state of Northern Qi.
Slovenia: The first wave of Slavic settlement, originating from Moravia, reaches the Eastern Alps region and the western margin of the Pannonian plain.
Vietnam: Triệu Việt Vương expelled Liang forces from Vạn Xuân and reestablished the capital at Long Biên.
